    "shortDesc": "Gastritis, unspecified, without bleeding",
    "longDesc": "Gastritis, unspecified, without bleeding",
    "plainEnglish": "Gastritis is inflammation of the stomach lining that causes discomfort, pain, or burning sensations in your upper abdomen. When a doctor uses this code, they've identified that you have stomach inflammation but haven't specified the exact cause (such as an infection, medication, stress, or alcohol use), and importantly, there is no active bleeding occurring.",
    "whoUses": "Primary care physicians, gastroenterologists, and emergency medicine doctors use this code when evaluating patients with stomach pain or upper abdominal discomfort. It commonly appears on patient EOBs when someone visits for digestive complaints and receives a diagnosis of non-bleeding gastritis without a more specific underlying cause being documented.",
