    "shortDesc": "Other diseases of stomach and duodenum",
    "longDesc": "Other diseases of stomach and duodenum",
    "plainEnglish": "This code covers less common stomach and duodenum (the first part of the small intestine) conditions that don't fit into other specific categories. These might include unusual inflammation, functional disorders, or structural problems that affect how your stomach digests food or how food moves from your stomach into the intestines, causing symptoms like pain, bloating, nausea, or difficulty eating.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists and primary care physicians use this code when diagnosing stomach or duodenal problems that don't match more specific diagnoses. It's a catch-all code that appears on EOB statements for patients undergoing endoscopy, experiencing chronic stomach issues, or having conditions that need further investigation or don't fit standard diagnostic categories.",
