    "shortDesc": "Dvrtclos of lg int w/o perforation or abscess w/o bleeding",
    "longDesc": "Diverticulosis of large intestine without perforation or abscess without bleeding",
    "plainEnglish": "Diverticulosis means you have small pouches (called diverticula) that have formed in the walls of your large intestine (colon), but they are not currently infected, ruptured, or causing bleeding. These pouches develop over time when weak spots in the intestinal wall bulge outward, often due to increased pressure from constipation or straining. Many people with diverticulosis have no symptoms at all, though some may experience mild abdominal discomfort or bloating.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists, colorectal surgeons, and primary care physicians commonly use this code when documenting findings from colonoscopy or CT imaging. It appears regularly on patient EOB statements and is often used to track the condition during routine screening or when patients report digestive symptoms.",
