    "shortDesc": "Constipation, unspecified",
    "longDesc": "Constipation, unspecified",
    "plainEnglish": "Constipation means your bowel movements are infrequent, difficult, or involve passing hard, dry stools. This can happen for many reasons—like not drinking enough water, not eating enough fiber, not exercising, certain medications, or changes in routine—and it causes discomfort, straining, or a feeling that you can't fully empty your bowels.",
