    "rawCode": "K635",
    "shortDesc": "Polyp of colon",
    "longDesc": "Polyp of colon",
    "plainEnglish": "A polyp of the colon is a small, usually benign growth that develops on the inner lining of your large intestine (colon). Most colon polyps don't cause symptoms and are discovered during a colonoscopy screening, but some people may experience bleeding or changes in bowel habits. While many polyps are harmless, certain types can potentially develop into cancer over time, which is why doctors recommend regular screening and removal of polyps.",
    "whoUses": "Gastroenterologists and colorectal surgeons commonly use this code when diagnosing and treating colon polyps during colonoscopy procedures. The code frequently appears on patient EOB statements following screening colonoscopies or when polyps are identified and removed during endoscopic procedures.",
